  "final_answer": "## Annualized Q1 2026 Run-Rate vs. FY2025\n\n### Source figures (recast consolidated entity, including xAI and X Holdings)\nFrom the segment revenue disclosure in the SpaceX S-1:\n\n| Metric | Q1 2026 | FY2025 |\n|---|---|---|\n| Consolidated revenue | $4,694M | $18,674M |\n| Connectivity segment revenue | $3,257M | $11,387M |\n| Space segment revenue | $619M | $4,086M |\n| AI segment revenue | $818M | $3,201M |\n\n### Annualization (Q1 2026 × 4)\n\n| Metric | Annualized Q1 2026 | FY2025 | Implied YoY growth |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Consolidated revenue | $18,776M | $18,674M | **+0.55%** |\n| Connectivity revenue | $13,028M | $11,387M | **+14.41%** |\n| Space revenue | $2,476M | $4,086M | **−39.40%** |\n| AI revenue | $3,272M | $3,201M | **+2.22%** |\n\n### Decomposition of the consolidated growth rate (contribution to growth, in % of FY2025 base)\n\n| Segment | $ change (annualized vs. FY2025) | Contribution to consolidated growth |\n|---|---|---|\n| Connectivity | +$1,641M | +8.79% |\n| Space | −$1,610M | −8.62% |\n| AI | +$71M | +0.38% |\n| **Consolidated** | **+$102M** | **+0.55%** |\n\n### What the implied growth profile says about concentration of momentum\n\n1. **Consolidated growth is essentially flat (+0.55%), but it masks extreme dispersion across segments.** The headline run-rate barely moves versus FY2025, yet underneath, Connectivity is growing double digits while Space is contracting sharply and AI is roughly flat.\n\n2. **Connectivity is the sole meaningful source of consolidated momentum.** Connectivity's annualized run-rate implies +$1,641M of incremental revenue versus FY2025, which is ~16x the entire consolidated incremental revenue of +$102M. Connectivity alone accounts for ~95.9% of all positive segment growth (Connectivity + AI = $1,712M; Connectivity = $1,641M).\n\n3. **Space is a near-perfect offset to Connectivity.** Space's annualized run-rate implies −$1,610M versus FY2025, almost dollar-for-dollar canceling Connectivity's +$1,641M gain. The consolidated line is therefore a \"wash\" between a high-growth Connectivity franchise and a sharply decelerating/declining Space business.\n\n4. **Mix is shifting decisively toward Connectivity.** Connectivity's share of consolidated revenue rises from 60.98% in FY2025 to 69.39% on the Q1 2026 annualized run-rate — an ~8.4 percentage-point shift in a single quarter's annualization. This is consistent with Connectivity (Starlink) being the consolidated entity's growth engine, while the legacy launch/Space segment is contracting in the recast base.\n\n5. **Implication for the growth narrative.** The near-flat consolidated run-rate does **not** reflect broad-based stability; it reflects a concentrated, single-segment growth story (Connectivity) being diluted by a large offsetting decline in Space. Any deterioration in Connectivity's trajectory would translate almost one-for-one into consolidated deceleration, because the other segments are not contributing offsetting growth (Space is negative; AI is barely positive). Conversely, the consolidated growth profile is highly leveraged to Connectivity's continued expansion.\n\n### Caveats\n- Annualizing a single quarter assumes Q1 2026 is representative of the full year; the filing does not state seasonality assumptions, so the run-rate is a point-in-time inference rather than guidance.\n- All figures reflect the retrospectively recast consolidated entity (SpaceX + xAI + X Holdings) under common-control accounting; no period reflects standalone SpaceX operations.\n- The S-1 does not provide explicit FY2026 guidance, so the comparison is purely an implied run-rate analysis.\n\n{\n  \"sources\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\",\n      \"name\": \"SpaceX S-1 (filed May 20, 2026) — Segment revenue disclosure (Q1 2026 and FY2025)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
